<div class="row">
<div class="twelve columns">
<h4>Removing Borders and Shading</h4>
<p>If your cursor is at the end of the sentence when you select paragraph
shading or border, when you hit enter after the sentence, the border or shading
will continue on the next line. Your cursor is "trapped inside the
box."ù</p>

<p>To fix this, highlight the hidden "enter" character (∂) on the line
that shouldn't have the box, and go back to Borders and Shading to remove the
box or shading by selecting <strong>None</strong> or <strong>No Color</strong>. You must retrace your <strong>exact steps</strong> to undo the border or shading.</p>


